{
  "Question": "<p>How to show <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_471\"><math alttext=\"(a_{1}a_{2}\\ldots a_{n})^{\\frac{1}{n}}\\leq\\frac{\\sum_{i=1}^{n}a_{i}}{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></msup><mo>\u2264</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"false\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msubsup></mstyle><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span> with <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_472\"><math alttext=\"a_{i}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></semantics></math></span> positive.</p> <p>Well, I tried by induction: with <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_473\"><math alttext=\"n=2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_474\"><math alttext=\"\\sqrt{ab}\\leq\\frac{a+b}{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msqrt><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></msqrt><mo>\u2264</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span> is equivalent to say (elevate square in both side) <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_475\"><math alttext=\"4ab\\leq a^{2}+2ab+b^{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mo>\u2264</mo><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> and this is equivalent <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_476\"><math alttext=\"0\\leq(a-b)^{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>\u2264</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span> and this is true.</p> <p>I suppose it is true for some <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_477\"><math alttext=\"n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>n</mi></semantics></math></span>. But with <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_478\"><math alttext=\"n+1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>, I don't know how to do, Please can help me with a hint or other way, thank you so much.</p>",
  "Title": "How to show <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_470\"><math alttext=\"(a_{1}a_{2}\\ldots a_{n})^{\\frac{1}{n}}\\leq\\frac{\\sum_{i=1}^{n}a_{i}}{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></msup><mo>\u2264</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"false\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msubsup></mstyle><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
